CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 28, 1956, pg. 2, reads: "Judo Expert - Theodore A. Flewellen, 42, of 323 Renfrew St., displays his judo skills on fellow deputy sheriff 'Izzy' Moidell. Moidell, and ex-boxer and wrestler, and judo-expert Flewellen are members of Sheriff William Davis' staff which includes professional football players and just plain 'tough guys' who, besides their sidearms, possess certain skills which enable them to handle various types of law-breakers. - 'Teenie' Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Theodore A. Flewellen lifting Deputy Sheriff Izzy Moidell with judo maneuver, in office
